dialogue: How long have you lived in the area, Mr. Chicowski?
Ten years.
And you... run a flower shop?
Yes. With my wife.
Bet you never come home empty-handed on your anniversary...
Hey, it has been a minute. But I was hoping you could do me a solid...
... We cannot break the law. We can only break ourselves of the law...
It's okay, I'm not a juror anymore.
You made sure of that.
Feeling the pressure, huh?
In this job, always.
You got this case all wrong.
Really.
It was a hit and run.
No way. M.E. would've flagged it.
You'd think. But he did five autopsies that day. I checked.
Doesn't mean anything.
Let me ask you something: Did you look at ANY other suspects besides James Sythe?
We did our job.
If you'd done your job, we wouldn't be standing here right now.
The guy's bad news.
Maybe. Doesn’t mean he killed his girlfriend.
